Business Brief -- Lafarge Corp.:
   Construction Concern Posted
   Loss for 4th Quarter, Year
Lafarge President Robert W. Murdoch said the company is
still in "solid" financial shape and plans to limit its
capital spending. In New York Stock Exchange trading
yesterday, Lafarge shares closed down 25 cents at $13.50.
   Lafarge is a subsidiary of Lafarge Coppee S.A. of Paris.